![](results/7-4.png width=\pagewidth)

## Detection results (threshold = 20) 
![](results/7-5.png width=\pagewidth)
For each shift position of the small image every pixel in the small image is compared to the corresponding pixel in the large image subsection and SSD from all the pixels is computed. For each pixel, the sum of the differences of each color is computed and added together and the squared difference from all the pixels compared is totaled. The best match occurs where the SSD for that shift position is the smallest.

